title: For Sale:  BlackHawk Night-Ops Gladius Flashlight 75200OD
postcontent:
BlackHawk Night-Ops Gladius Flashlight 75200OD Green for sale. $150.00 obo retailed new for $235, but this model has been discontinued. But you can still get it here. You want it? Make me an offer, but please no trades, and try not to be a lowballer, that gets old. 

This has been used gently, has mostly sat in my bug out kit, has seen use while camping once, and during some bug out prep scenarios. Flashlight still functions flawlessly.

Product Information
Shop more BlackHawk products
The Gladius flashlight is packed with unique features including durable aluminum construction, fully-adjustable light intensity, automatic temperature control to avoid overheating, low battery indicator and a lock-out tail cap. Three operation modes provide momentary, constant-on and strobe functions. Run time: 90 minutes at full power, 400 hours at lowest setting (1 lumen). Length: 6-1/4". Weight: 6-1/2 oz. 

Technical Information

Bezel diameter: 1.25"
Tailcap diameter: 1.25"
Body diameter: 1"
Length (bezel to tailcap): 6.23"
Weight (without batteries): 6.63 oz

Material and operation: Aluminum, waterproof, LED bulbs. Tailcap has thumb-activated button and a rotary dial surrounding the button.

Settings:
Standard. Tailcap turned fully clockwise. Press button - on, release button - off
Strobe. Tailcap in center detent. When button is pressed, light is in strobe mode.
Constant On and adjustable light level. Tailcap is fully counter-clockwise. 
a. Quick press and release of button leaves light on, repeat and light goes off.
b. Hold down on the button and the light will stay on and begin to get dimmer. When at desired light level, release button. Light has 100:1 ratio from 4 watts to 0.03 watts and takes 3 seconds once the sequence is started. To make light brighter, hold button down and light will get brighter.
System Off. Press button halfway down when tailcap is fully counter-clockwise. This will unlock the tailcap and it can be turned even farther counter-clockwise. This will lock the button and it will not depress. This mode allows storage of the light in a gear bag without the light activating.

Other Features:
Auto temperature control. If the light temperature becomes excessive, control cuts LED power by 50% (25% light reduction), allowing the temperature to gradually reduce. Light will continue to operate.
If temperature continues to rise after the power reduction, power is automatically terminated to protect LED and surrounding materials. When the light has cooled, it can be returned to full power by depressing the tailcap button.
Low Battery. When the battery life reaches a pre-determined point (which will vary depending on usage), the light will pulse twice every 15 seconds until the batteries are replaced. This low battery indication is programmed for the momentary and constant modes only.
Run time. Approximately 90 minutes of full power outlet (90 lumens), with an additional 20 minutes of gradually reducing light output. Approximately 400+ hours at the lowest setting (approximately 1 lumen).

title: For Sale:  1944 Mosin Nagant m44
postcontent:
The 7.62x54r cartridge is a great bullet that shoots similar to the 30-06. Military surplus 7.62x54r is currently purchasable in the U.S. in 440 round spam cans for under $100. This ammo is imported from Soviet Union cold war stockpiles. Importantly, the cost translates to about .20 cents per round! 

What firearms shoot this great ammo? The Mosin Nagant is a high quality and affordable bolt-action rifle that shoots this inexpensive ammo. Currently, you can't afford a semi-automatic that shoots this round! The prices on semi-autos that shoot the 7.62x54r range from a low of $1000-$1500 (i.e., PSL, VEPR-54, SVT-40) to $5000 (i.e., NDM-86, TIGR) and upwards of $20,000 (SVD Dragunov).

For sale here is a 1944 year model m44 Mosin Nagant. It is in very nice (collectable) condition. It includes the sling and bayonet. It was made at Izhevsk and is all numbers matching. The gun shows little signs of usage and has a beautiful stock. 

Transaction: Private transaction, Face-to-face, no shipping, Arkansas resident legal to own, price is firm.

If you want to buy this rifle: Email me that you are legal to own and an Arkansas resident and include your contact information. Please no solicitations or questions from data collectors.

title: For Sale:  Llama 3A .380(micro 1911 style)
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
I am only selling this to fund another purchase. It is in extremely nice condition and I have never had a malfunction with it.

This little Llama .380 was made in 1974. Why is that important? It was the last year that they made it with a true 1911 style locked-breech action. After this, Llama cheapened them up by making them a blowback. The locked breech is more accurate, stronger, and more reliable than what came later. It also seems to have much less felt recoil. I have owned both and there is a significant difference, with the earlier guns like this one being much better in all categories. 

This one has factory adjustable sights and is a dream to shoot. I shoot empty shotgun shells with it at 25 yards all the time.

I am available to meet you almost any time here in Santa Fe.

Contact me through Armslist with your phone number and I will call you so we can meet. You will like it. It's tiny, but it seems to fit most hands, and is a great car gun or concealed carry gun. Everyone who has evr held this one has commented on how comfortable it is, and how nice the trigger is.  I am cheap on this one. Very cheap, and I know it - so the price is firm.

Thanks very much for looking!

Doby Pilgrim
Santa Fe
